76561197970736031,Recommended,235620,10161672,"Posted: 18 May, 2014",all,McKeifus,"This is one of my favorite board games.  Hands down.  It is not without its issues, but they will not stop me from playing it.That said, the game is very luck based, reducing the strategy element.  Combo selection is critical, but can be very random.  If they removed the die, and went to a bidding system instead of the coin-drop, the game would be much more strategic.  Hopefully they can add a gamemode for hardcore strategists some day.For 2 players, the game falls apart pretty fast.  Combo selection owns, and some combos are just broken.  At 3 players this abates with the introduction of some classic game theory situations - the ability to gang up on a third player.Overall this is a GREAT and fun game.  Emphasis on fun - even with the randomness it is wildly entertaining.  I picked it up for 7 bucks and it has been one of the best purchases on Steam thus far."
