,Recommended,235620,28677767,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,Theck,"If you're a fan of the board game, you'll love this digital version. Gameplay is speedier thanks to the computer handling the basic rules and accounting for you. And of course, the big benefit is being able to play a game with friends (or strangers) remotely rather than having to wait for game night.Only gripe is that the game is still a bit buggy. I've had some oddities when starting games where the game begins, but it doesn't switch from the lobby to the game board screen. This was easily fixed by backing out and re-entering through the ""Games in Progress"" panel, but it probably wouldn't work for arena mode. I've also had it drop me out of an arena game against a friend, erroneously claiming I lost my internet connection."
