,Recommended,235620,34340223,Posted: 18 August,all,›яR‹ BamH1,"A great adaption of an excellent Euro-style game that has an amusing satirical Fantasy theme.Excellent replayability with randomised factions every play through. In fact Days of Wonder should consider adding the realms expansion as a further DLC to introduce a randomised board for even greater replayability.I own the adroid app also and the windows interface does have some minor bugs in the PC port such as missing scroll bars in the stats and credits and it is wierd not having an actual ""exit"" or ""quit"" button. But these are minor. There are tons of play options for networked and friend play and even some unusal ones like pass and play (a hang-over from the mobile dev).I have not seen any credit to the original contestant winners for the conceptualisation of the expansion races and powers, but hopefully that was merely an oversight.This is a great casual game and a great example of how modern board games have evolved well beyond the traditional ""roll and move"" paradigm."
